{{Infobox ecoregion |name = Ecoregion: Caucasus mixed forests |image = Бадукское озеро.jpg |image_size = 300 |image_alt = |caption = Lake Baduksko, in [[Teberda Nature Reserve]], [[Karachay-Cherkessia]], Russia |map = File:Ecoregion PA0408.png.jpg |map_size = 300 |map_alt = Ecoregion territory (in yellow) |map_caption = Ecoregion territory (in yellow) |ecozone = Palearctic |biome = [[Temperate broadleaf and mixed forests]] |animals = |bird_species = |mammal_species = |border = |borders = |area = 170421 |country = |countries = Russia, Georgia, Azerbaijan, Turkey, Armenia |state = |region_type = |elevation = |coordinates = {{coords|41.75|44.25|display=title}} |geology = |seas = |rivers = |climate = |soil = |conservation = |global200 = |habitat_loss = |habitat_loss_ref = |protected = |protected_ref = }} The '''Caucasus mixed forests''' [[terrestrial ecoregion|ecoregion]], in the [[Temperate broadleaf and mixed forests]] [[Biome]], of [[Eurasia]] in [[Western Asia]] and [[Eastern Europe]]. It covers the [[Caucasus Mountains]] range, which forms the traditional border between [[Europe]] and [[Asia]], as well as the adjacent [[Lesser Caucasus]] range and the eastern end of the [[Pontic Mountains]]. As such, its highest point is [[Mount Elbrus]].<ref name="WWF, Caucasus MF">{{WWF ecoregion |name=Caucasus mixed forests |id=pa0408}}</ref><ref name="gs1">{{cite web|title=Caucasus mixed forests|url=https://www.globalspecies.org/ecoregions/display/PA0408|publisher=GlobalSpecies.org|language=en|access-date=October 23, 2018}}</ref>
==Distribution== Having the [[Lagodekhi Protected Areas]], [[Borjomi-Kharagauli National Park|Borjomi-Kharagauli]] and [[Tusheti National Park]]s, and [[Zagatala State Reserve|Zakatala]] and [[Caucasus Biosphere Reserve]]s,<ref name="WWF, Caucasus MF"/> the ecoregion covers an area of {{convert|170,300|km2|sqmi|sp=us}}, extending across portions of: * [[Abkhazia]] * [[Armenia]] * [[Azerbaijan]] * [[Georgia (country)|Georgia]] * [[Iran]] * [[Russia]] * [[Turkey]]
