{{GeoGroupTemplate}} There are 40 [[national park]]s in [[Finland]]. They are all managed by the [[Metsähallitus]]. The national parks cover a total area of {{convert|9892|km2|sqmi|0}} – 2.7% of Finland's total land area. A total of 1.7 million people visited the parks in 2007.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.metsa.fi/news.asp?Section=10&Item=6348|title= Kansallispuistojen suosio kasvussa|accessdate= February 18, 2008|date= 2008-02-18|language= Finnish|publisher= [[Metsähallitus]]|deadurl= yes|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20080303202608/http://www.metsa.fi/news.asp?Section=10|archivedate= March 3, 2008|df= }}</ref> {{clear}} [[Image:Koli rotated.jpg|thumb|800px|center|Lake [[Pielinen]] seen from a hill in [[Koli National Park]].]]
